      <description xml:id="main">
         <coverage/>
         <attributes>
            <attribute label="Abstract" name="abstract">
               <value>
                  <attribute-value name="abstract">This manuscript contains the third part of the Hebrew Bible known
                            as Writings (Ketuvim) with numerous marginal glosses in Hebrew and
                            Judeo-Persian. It was copied by Jacob ben Obadiah ben Joseph ben Ezra in
                            the school of Rabbi Mordechai in Kashan in Iran at the request of Rav
                            Samuel ha-Levi. He completed his copy on Tuesday 2 July 1495. The order
                            in which the Bible books appear is as follows: Psalms (folios <a href="cudl:///page?n=1b">1b-72b</a>), Proverbs (folios <a href="cudl:///page?n=73a">73a-101b</a>), Ruth (folios <a href="cudl:///page?n=102b">102b-105b</a>), Song of Songs (folios
                                <a href="cudl:///page?n=105b">105b-109b</a>), Ecclesiastes
                            (folios <a href="cudl:///page?n=109b">109b-117a</a>), Lamentations
                            (folios <a href="cudl:///page?n=117b">117b-121b</a>), Esther (folios
                                <a href="cudl:///page?n=122b">122b-131a</a>), Daniel (folios
                                <a href="cudl:///page?n=131b">131b-150a</a>), Ezra (folios <a href="cudl:///page?n=150b">150b-161b</a>), Nehemiah (folios <a href="cudl:///page?n=161a">161b-179a</a>), Job (folios <a href="cudl:///page?n=179a">179a-209b</a>), 1 and 2 Chronicles (folios
                                <a href="cudl:///page?n=109b">209b-290b</a>). The biblical text
                            is vocalised and accompanied by masorah. According to Moses Gaster, this
                            is a unique manuscript showing the vocalisation and accentuation
                            tradition of Ben Naphtali.</attribute-value>
               </value>
            </attribute>
